comments: Sabonis (IND) places a resting hand on Green's (DEN) body and marginal contact occurs as he collapses it to absorb the contact during the driving shot attempt.
Dozier (DEN) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Brogdon (IND).
Turner (IND) briefly grasps and immediately releases Green's (DEN) jersey and the contact is marginal as it does not affect Green's ability to set his intended pick.
Green (DEN) establishes himself in a screening position in McConnell's (IND) path and absorbs the contact.
Sabonis (IND) swipes down and makes clean ball contact before cleanly blocking Morris' (DEN) driving shot attempt.
Green (DEN) maintains a legal guarding position on Brogdon (IND) during the drive.
As they approach the pick, Green (DEN) and Sabonis (IND) engage and disengage, and the contact is marginal.
Brogdon (IND) throws an errant pass that goes into the backcourt without being touched by a defender and a backcourt violation is correctly called.
Sabonis (IND) brings his arm down and makes contact with Barton's (DEN) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.

Replay review of the foul called on Green (DEN) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. Morris (DEN) jumps alongside of Sabonis (IND) and any marginal contact is created by Sabonis' leg extending out slightly. Green (DEN) makes clean ball contact, while avoiding any contact with Sabonis' head, to block the shot near the basket.
Gordon (DEN) establishes himself in a screening position in Holiday's (IND) path and absorbs the contact.
Sabonis (IND) is in the lane for longer than three seconds.
Barton (DEN) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Lamb (IND).

Green (DEN) reaches for the ball and marginal contact occurs as he brushes Lamb's (IND) arm, which does not affect his ability to maintain full control of the ball after gathering it against his body.
Brogdon (IND) stops his forward momentum and marginal contact occurs as he releases from Gordon (DEN) at the end of the drive.

Gordon (DEN) extends his arms out and makes clean ball contact while simultaneously brushing Brogdon's (IND) shoulder. The contact is marginal and does not affect Brogdon's ability to get into his upward shooting motion.
Barton (DEN) maintains a legal guarding position during the play at the basket by Brogdon (IND).
Holiday (IND) commits a take foul on Hyland (DEN).
Hyland (DEN) commits a take foul on Duarte (IND). The foul occurs prior to Duarte starting his upward shooting motion and a personal foul is correctly called.
